==English==

===Etymology===
Old English ''babewin'', ''baboin''; from French ''babouin'', or Late Latin ''babewynus''. Of unknown origin; [[cf.]] Dutch ''baviaan'', German ''pavian'', baboon, French ''babine'' lip of ape, dogs, etc., dial. German ''bäppe'' mouth.


===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}

#(''[[Zoological]]'') Mostly African [[primate]]s. One of the Old World [[Quadrumana]], of the genera [[Cynocephalus]] and [[Papio]]; the [[dog]]-faced [[ape]]. Baboons have dog-like [[muzzle]]s and large [[canine]] teeth, cheek pouches, a short tail, and naked [[callosities]] on the [[buttocks]]. 

